eirs of walāyah and by proposing new definitions of the "seal of God's friends" (khātim al-awliyā' Allāh), al- Mu'ayyad broadened the contexts of making esoteric knowledge public and shifted the apocalyptic frameworks of Islamic messianism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFatimitesxIntellectual life. 0aShīʻahxDoctrinesxSources. 0aShīʻahxDoctrinesxSources. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : History of Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2017z978311149102840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438466286423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438466286/original  a978-3-11-149102-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles